   "viva": "Examiner: 'POD5, sudden SOB, sats 90%, chest clear, CXR normal — what next and why?' — name PE, justify with the clear-chest-disproportionate-hypoxia logic, apply Wells, go to CTPA (note post-op D-dimer is near-useless), and ISBAR escalate. Consent/risk angle if anticoagulating or thrombolysing.",
