   "subarea": "Open disclosure & M&M",
   "trap": "RECENT CHANGE: From 30 November 2022, Victorian health service entities have a LEGAL (statutory) duty of candour for a Serious Adverse Patient Safety Event (SAPSE), under amendments to the Health Services Act 1988 (Vic). Unlike the voluntary national Open Disclosure Framework, the SDC is mandatory and prescriptive: a genuine apology within 24h, OFFER a meeting within 3 business days, HOLD it within 10 business days, and provide a WRITTEN ACCOUNT (facts + apology + description of the response + steps to prevent recurrence). The gotcha: the apology under SDC is still legally protected (not an admission of liability), and SAPSE review documents get statutory protection from disclosure. This is Victoria-specific — don’t state it as national law.",
